//2. What technologies are most websites composed of?

//Most websites are composed of HTML, CSS, and Javascript.

//3. Write the outline for an html page that connects both the CSS and js pages

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>

    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="checkpoint.css">
    <title>ID Card</title>
</head>
<body>
</body>
<script src='checkpoint.js' defer></script>
</html>

//4. Describe a parent vs a child element

HTML runs in a hierachical structure.  The "parent" element contains other elements within it that are referred to as "child" elements.  For example, in question 3, a parent element is 'html,' while it children are 'head,''body,' and 'script.'

//5.  Describe event bubbling.

Event bubbling refers to how DOM and Javascript handles the flow of HTML elements.  By default, when an event occurs, the event is triggered on that element and works its way up from the innermost element (children) to the outermost element (parent).


//6.  Using div tags and CSS, make a solid red circle inside of a green square

HTML: 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>

    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="checkpoint.css">
    <title>ID Card</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="square">
        <div class="circle"></div>
    </div>
</body>
<script src='script.js' defer></script>
</html>


CSS:

.square {
height: 500px;
width: 500px;
background-color: green;

}
.circle {
display: block;
background-color: red;
height: 300px;
width: 300px;
border-radius: 200px;
}




