    height: 100vh;
    position: absolute;
}





//8. What is an anchor tag and why do we use them?

Anchor tags create links to other websites or different parts of a webpage. We use them to access other websites, or specific sections of a webpage.

//9. What is the difference between an id and a class and when would you use which?

Id and classes are attributes that identify specific elements in HTML.  Creating an id is great for assigning a unique name to a value, while class can specify one or more class names for an element.
  I'd use id if there is an element that requires unique styling.  I'd use class when I wouldn't mind applying similar styling to multiple elements.


//10. Create both an id and a class and then access them in CSS

For an id:
<img id="littleboat" src="littleboat.jpg" alt="littleboat">
To acccess in CSS: #littleboat

For a class:
<img class="littleduck" src="littleduck.jpg" alt="littleduck">
To access in CSS: .littleduck

//11. Give an example of a block element and an inline element?

An example of a block element is div, which can be used to create a box whose dimensions (e.g. height, width) can be modified.  They start on a new line.
An example of an inline element is button, which appears inline with text of other elements.